  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (configuration gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver relies on three tunable configuration parameters: (1) near-wall mesh sizing (y+ target), (2) Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law exponent threshold for RBC damage onset, and (3) a convergence residual tolerance. Validation activities were executed at specific chosen settings for these parameters; however, the package does not bind or document those settings as deployment constraints, and the Context of Use does not restrict which parameter values must be used in production runs.",
