      "name": "Bench hemolysis correlation — at the chosen solver settings",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. At the chosen settings (y+ target, damage threshold exponent, and residual tolerance selected by the analyst), mean NIH error was 8.3% and all RH values remained below 1.0. Validation is reported at these settings; no configuration node is linked to constrain reuse.",
