      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity study — near-wall y+ sweep",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (coarse y+=5, medium y+=2, fine y+=1) were evaluated. The medium y+=2 mesh was selected as the production mesh on grounds of cost-accuracy balance. The validation package records this selection in narrative form only; no formal configuration binding links the y+=2 setting to the deployment model, and the convergence residual tolerance (set to 1e-5 during validation) is not documented as a required deployment parameter.",
