    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. The CFD model predicts hemolysis within experimental uncertainty across all 5 COU operating points, and RH < 1.0 is satisfied. The assessment team notes that solver configuration parameters (near-wall mesh y+ target, Giersiepen–Wurzinger damage exponent, and iterative convergence tolerance) were set to specific values during validation and are described in simulation narratives, but these values have not been formally bound or documented as required deployment constraints. The team considers this acceptable given the bench test corroboration and the medium model influence designation, and the package is accepted at Medium assurance level.",
